subSubSection.paragraph:
Cell V oval, about half of the length of cell IV, not connected with cell III. Outer appendage unbranched, up to 500 µm long. Inner appendage consisting of a small basal cell supporting two to a few branches, simple or scarcely divided into pairs or small clusters of terminal antheridia; sometimes bearing long sterile branches. [Detailed descriptions: 
Majewski 1994b
; 
Santamaria 1998
]
